<subSubSection lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="626" pageId="14" pageNumber="625" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,290,468,492]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Description.</emphasis>
Colouration (
<figureCitation box="[437,515,468,492]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[151,190,1523,1542]" captionTargetBox="[250,1033,230,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-10@16.[151,1126,206,1500]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs.18-21. Habitus.18 – Physopelta kotheae sp. nov. (J, 14.03 mm); 19 – Ph. cincticollis Stål, 1863 (J, 12.0 mm); 20 – Ph. melanopyga rufifemur subsp. nov. (holotype, ♀, 16.97 mm); 21 – Ph. trimaculata sp. nov. (holotype, J, 13.79 mm). Photo: L. Dembický (18-19, 21) and J. Kabíček (20)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341849/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Black colour on head, antennae (except of slightly more than apical half of antennomere IV which is white), callar lobe, large oval median and smaller oval apical spot on corium, legs, sternum, ventrites (except of laterotergites), and membrane (except of slightly paler veins). Pronotal lobe and scutellum (except of apex) darkened. All pronotal margins, scutellar apex, clavus and corium, anal vein, postcubital vein and claval comissure on clavus, cubital vein on corium, and costal margins yellowish; both clavus and corium basally and between median and apical spot darker. Anterior margin of callar lobe reddish. Labium pale reddish or black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Structure. Body large and robust; antennae and legs stout. Antennomere 1 shorter, distinctly widening towards apex. Profemora in both sexes very stout, dorsal margin of longitudinal furrow with indicated denticles along its entire length, only apically with two strong teeth; ventral margin of longitudinal furrow along its entire length with medium-sized, somewhat curved teeth and small denticles. Meso- and metafemora ventrally along its entire length with shallow, wider impression, bordered on both sides with small denticles (slightly smaller in females). Labial segment I not approaching head base. Callar lobe strongly gibbous in both sexes; pronotal lobe nearly flat, with indicated median longitudinal ridge.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">
Pygophore. Ventral wall nearly flat, ventral rim nearly horizontally inclined into genital chamber, with bowl-shaped depression, medially ridge-like gibbous. Lateral rim rounded, median part of lower margin of lateral rim infolding elevated dorsally. Paramere stout, basally almost parallel-sided, outer side distinctly incrassate, apically narrowed, round and straight, apex rounded; the opposite side under the narrowed apical part distinctly arcuately gibbous (
<figureCitation box="[159,238,1140,1164]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[113,152,1503,1522]" captionTargetBox="[110,1086,210,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-13@11.[92,1089,187,1413]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 11-17. Parameres. 11 – Delacampius siberutensis sp. nov.; 12-13 – Iphita heissi sp. nov. (two different views); 14 – I. varians varians (Breddin, 1901); 15 – Physopelta kotheae sp. nov.; 16 – Ph. cincticollis Stål, 1863; 17 – Ph. trimaculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341847/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Punctation. Pronotal lobe, scutellum, clavus and corium with distinct black and coarse punctures, those on pronotal lobe and scutellum uniformly dense. Costal margin of corium impunctate.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Pilosity. Dorsal surface of body covered with black erect hairs, only posterior pronotal margin with row of horizontal pale hairs. Ventrites with pale adpressed and longer erect hairs.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Measurements (all in mm). Males (n = 5). Body length 14.03 (12.80-14.85); head: width (including eyes) 2.15 (2.07-2.24), interocular width 1.36 (1.27-1.43); lengths of antennomeres: 1 – 2.13 (2.00-2.21), 2 – 2.40 (2.21-2.54), 3 – 1.63 (1.57-1.67), 4 – 2.60 (2.43-2.75); pronotum: length 3.00 (2.70-3.40), width 4.39 (4.10-4.75); scutellum: length 2.14 (1.97-2.38), width 2.61 (2.48-2.97); corium: length 7.20 (6.86-7.67), width 2.51 (2.43-2.62).</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1128,468,1548]" lastBlockId="15.[113,1089,219,788]" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="626" pageId="14" pageNumber="625">Females (n = 5). Body length 14.19 (13.55-14.63); head: width (including eyes) 2.18 (2.08-2.24), interocular width 1.41 (1.35-1.46); lengths of antennomeres: 1 – 1.94 (1.57-2.11), 2 – 2.33 (2.16-2.48), 3 – 1.61 (1.40-1.73), 4 – 2.64 (2.54-2.70); pronotum: length 2.79 (2.56- 2.97), width 4.39 (4.10-4.59); scutellum: length 2.15 (1.94-2.29), width 2.43 (2.16-2.75); corium: length 7.19 (6.80-7.67), width 2.46 (2.29-2.59).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="626" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[113,1089,219,788]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[113,363,315,339]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species is related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Stal, 1863" authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[677,1031,314,340]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cincticollis">
<emphasis box="[677,918,317,340]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Physopelta cincticollis</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="STAL C." box="[924,1031,314,339]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" pagination="390 - 404" refId="ref20239" refString="STAL C. 1863: Beitrag zur Kenntnis der Pyrrhocoriden. Berliner Entomologische Zeitschrift 7: 390 - 404." type="journal article" year="1863">Stål, 1863</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="16.[151,190,1523,1542]" captionTargetBox="[250,1033,230,1497]" captionTargetId="figure-10@16.[151,1126,206,1500]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Figs.18-21. Habitus.18 – Physopelta kotheae sp. nov. (J, 14.03 mm); 19 – Ph. cincticollis Stål, 1863 (J, 12.0 mm); 20 – Ph. melanopyga rufifemur subsp. nov. (holotype, ♀, 16.97 mm); 21 – Ph. trimaculata sp. nov. (holotype, J, 13.79 mm). Photo: L. Dembický (18-19, 21) and J. Kabíček (20)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341849" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341849/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
), which is widely distributed from eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[612,667,347,371]" name="India" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">India</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[704,767,348,371]" name="Japan" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[780,848,348,371]" name="South Korea" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Korea</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[860,941,347,371]" name="Taiwan" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, and Sumatra (KERZHNER 2001, 
<bibRefCitation author="STEHLIK J. L." box="[304,461,379,404]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" pagination="141 - 160" refId="ref20320" refString="STEHLIK J. L. 2005 a: Largidae and Pyrrhocoridae of Laos (Hemiptera: Heteroptera). Folia Heyrovskyana 12 (4) (2004): 141 - 160." type="journal article" year="2005">STEHLÍK 2005a</bibRefCitation>
) and differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík &amp; Jindra, 2008" authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2008" box="[659,787,381,404]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotheae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[659,787,381,404]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. kotheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[795,879,380,403]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by its smaller size, distinctly slender antennae and legs. Additional characters that can distinguish the two species are as follows: antennomere 1 slender and regularly widening towards apex in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[931,1089,445,468]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cincticollis">
<emphasis box="[931,1089,445,468]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. cincticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(stouter and distinctly widened apically in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík &amp; Jindra, 2008" authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2008" box="[575,702,477,500]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotheae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[575,702,477,500]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. kotheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[710,798,476,500]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); apices of profemora with two medium-sized, well separated teeth ventrally (with two large teeth placed side-by-side in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík &amp; Jindra, 2008" authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2008" box="[142,269,541,564]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotheae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[142,269,541,564]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. kotheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[276,363,540,564]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); distinctly slender tibiae with more slender spines (stout with very conspicuous spines in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík &amp; Jindra, 2008" authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2008" box="[357,485,573,596]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotheae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[357,485,573,596]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. kotheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[493,581,572,596]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); anterior portion of pronotum much narrower, callar lobe less gibbous, lateral margins of pronotum from the level of pronotal lobe distinctly widening towards pronotal base, especially in females (pronotal margins less widening posteriorly in 
<taxonomicName authority="Stehlík &amp; Jindra, 2008" authorityName="Stehlík &amp; Jindra" authorityYear="2008" box="[268,396,669,692]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kotheae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[268,396,669,692]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. kotheae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[405,494,668,692]" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
); longitudinal furrow on meso- and metafemora much narrower; paramere of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Stal" authorityYear="1863" box="[358,518,701,724]" class="Insecta" family="Largidae" genus="Physopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="626" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cincticollis">
<emphasis box="[358,518,701,724]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Ph. cincticollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as in 
<figureCitation box="[581,660,699,723]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="11.[113,152,1503,1522]" captionTargetBox="[110,1086,210,1405]" captionTargetId="figure-13@11.[92,1089,187,1413]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figs. 11-17. Parameres. 11 – Delacampius siberutensis sp. nov.; 12-13 – Iphita heissi sp. nov. (two different views); 14 – I. varians varians (Breddin, 1901); 15 – Physopelta kotheae sp. nov.; 16 – Ph. cincticollis Stål, 1863; 17 – Ph. trimaculata sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5341847" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5341847/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="626">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
